# sbperf auth + options. Copy to `.env` (gitignored) and fill in.
# Bun auto-loads `.env`, so these become process.env for `bun run src/index.ts`.

# --- Auth (pick ONE) ---
# 1. Personal Access Token: https://supabase.com/dashboard/account/tokens
# SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN=sbp_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
#
# 2. OR leave it unset and run `supabase login` - sbperf reads the CLI token
#    from ~/.supabase/access-token automatically. (Resolution: env var first,
#    then the CLI token.)

# --- Superuser SQL tier (optional; your own projects) ---
# The default SQL tier is the PAT read-only runner (no password). For full
# access on a project you own, put the supabase_admin (or any Postgres)
# connection string here. QUOTE it (single quotes) so `$` / special chars in
# the password aren't shell-interpolated. --db-url overrides this if both given.
# The PAT is still used for API planes + metrics; the connstring is NEVER
# written to analysis.json (only which tier was used).
# SBPERF_DB_URL='postgresql://supabase_admin:PASSWORD@aws-0-REGION.pooler.supabase.com:6543/postgres'

# --- narrate (optional; LLM synthesis over analysis.json -> narrative.md) ---
# `sbperf narrate <dir>` uses any OpenAI-compatible /chat/completions endpoint
# (OpenAI, a local llama-server, OpenRouter, ...). BASE_URL + MODEL required;
# API_KEY optional (local servers usually need none). Not used by any other
# command; the deterministic report never calls an LLM.
# SBPERF_LLM_BASE_URL=http://localhost:11434/v1
# SBPERF_LLM_MODEL=your-model-id
# SBPERF_LLM_API_KEY=sk-xxxx
